                            <comment id="15690650" author="mgohin" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 16:38:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Used acroForm.flatten(); to transform the pdf as readonly&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15691182" author="tilman" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 19:41:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please attach a PDF where you applied the permissions. Also have a look at your saved PDF with Adobe Reader, Document properties, security.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15691398" author="mgohin" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 21:22:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Generated file with permissions and without flatten option&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15691399" author="mgohin" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 21:23:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added the file, updated the gist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I can still edit fields :/&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15691424" author="tilman" created="Wed, 23 Nov 2016 21:35:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Please add &lt;tt&gt;setCanModifyAnnotations(false);&lt;/tt&gt; and test again.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The specification and/or our documentation is confusing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bit 6: Add or modify text annotations, fill in interactive form fields, and, if bit 4 is also set, create or modify interactive form fields (including signature fields).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Bit 9: (Security handlers of revision 3 or greater) Fill in existing interactive form fields (including signature fields), even if bit 6 is clear.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You had unset bit 9 but set bit 6.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15692604" author="mgohin" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2016 08:14:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;And that&apos;s it.&lt;br/&gt;
My need is to flatten the pdf but you found the solution.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PDFBox should add a clearer doc maybe ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your help&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
